      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like the failure of your company is deeply tied to your sense of self-worth and identity. The shame and guilt you're feeling are not just about the financial consequences, but also about the person you thought you were and the expectations you had for yourself. It can be incredibly painful to acknowledge that your identity was built on something that's now been torn away. Allow yourself to feel the weight of this grief and disappointment - it's acknowledgeing your pain that can be the first step towards moving forward.",
      "source": "target",
